Class FileInput

  • java.lang.Object
    • FileInput

  • public class FileInput
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is used to create an object that references another file. It contains method for extracting data from said file.

      FileInput(java.lang.String fileName)

    • Constructor Detail

      • FileInput

        public FileInput(java.lang.String fileName)
        Constructor that tries to open a file with the given filename. If it can be opened a reader is instanced to be utilized by the classes other methods to navigate a file.
        Parameters:
        fileName - the name of the desired file to be read.
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - If encountered the filename, and exception name are printed
        java.lang.Exception - If any other exceptions are encountered a stack trace is spit out.

    • Method Detail

      • getFileName

        The name of the file being read.

      • fileRead

        public void fileRead()
        reads and prints out the contents of the file to the console.
        Throws:

      • fileReadLine

        public java.lang.String fileReadLine()
        Reads through a file and returns the line to wherever the method is called so information from the file can be parsed and operated on by the JVM.
        Returns:
        The current line being read by the buffer.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Will output the exception name and the filename if an exception is encountered.

      • fileClose

        public void fileClose()
        Tries to close the file after the read.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an IOException is encountered this method spits out a stack trace.
